cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL 

This paper is primarily focused on computer vision, specifically on understanding the information represented and processed in CNNs. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Additionally, the paper explores the use of information theoretic techniques developed in the field of neuroscience, which suggests a potential overlap with cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also discusses the need for explainable AI, which could place it in the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper uses visualization techniques to understand the inner workings of the CNN, which could also place it in the sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language).
